A shower will appear larger than it actually is if the pan's surface is unbroken by a drain-hole. The best way to do that is to build a drain grate or gutter into the floor under where the shower base meets the wall. Experts advise using a 2 per cent gradient towards the gutter. READ: 7 couches to make your friends jealous! If the gutter is instead installed between the shower base and the rest of the bathroom, the gradient should be reduced to 0.5 per cent, but no less. That will prevent water surging beyond the shower area onto the floor in the rest of the room.